  "time_ut": 1661667998,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bcd \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bc7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The stateless race is the Tamil race",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Member of Parliament of the Tamil National Federation I. Sanakyan has publicly called for all the lakhs of Tamils \u200b\u200bliving outside Sri Lanka to unite.",
        "He made this call while speaking as a special guest at the Tamil Street Festival held in Canada.",
        "If we say that there is no nation in this world, it is our Tamil race. It is our unfortunate fate. We live in all countries of the world. We have parliamentary representation in all countries. We have representatives in all provinces and states. But till today we are without a country of our own.",
        "You know our people who were driven out by war in the past, who were sent as refugees from our country, are in the best place in the world today.",
        "It is a matter of pride for all of us to say that Sri Lankan government today relies on the investments of Tamils. One thing I often say about Sri Lanka. it is all fate. It was my destiny to become a Member of Parliament. Today I am speaking from Canada. Similarly, a political solution for the Tamils \u200b\u200bin Sri Lanka will surely be found. We all have to fight together until we get it.",
        "If I say that I believe in destiny, then Gotabaya Rajapaksa, who drove us out of our country and our territories, has left the same country and taken refuge in another country as a refugee.",
        "Today, the same people who voted for Gotabaya Rajapaksa have driven him out of the country. That is the rule. We are moving towards a dignified political solution in our country.",
        "I would like to publicly state here that our political journey will continue until we establish a permanent, peaceful, and a better future for the Tamil people living in our country through that honorable political solution.",
        "To get our political solution in Sri Lanka we need to work together again as we have done together in the past. The Tamil people living in Sri Lanka are relying on you. They expect your support. Only through your support will a permanent political solution be found. Until then we will all fight together. Long live Tamil"
      ],
